  "prompt": "How do I add question details digitally on Quora?",
  "response": "To add question details digitally on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to your Quora account**: Make sure you are logged in to your Quora account. If you don't have an account, you'll need to create one.\n\n2. **Navigate to the question**: Use the search bar at the top of the page to find the question you want to add details to. You can type in keywords or the full question text.\n\n3. **Click on the question**: Once you find the question, click on it to go to its page.\n\n4. **Add details**:\n   - If you are the person who asked the question, you'll see an \"Edit question\" button near the top of the page. Click on it.\n   - A dialog box will appear where you can edit the question text and add details. Look for the \"Add details\" or \"Question details\" section.\n   - Type in the additional information you want to provide. Be clear and concise to help others understand your question better.\n   - After adding the details, click \"Save\" or \"Done\" to update the question.\n\n5. **Review your changes**: The details you added should now appear below the question text on the question page.\n\nIf you're not the person who asked the question but want to provide additional context or information, you can do so by adding an answer or a comment:\n\n- **Add an answer**: Click on the \"Answer\" button below the question and write your response. You can include the additional details in your answer.\n- **Add a comment**: Below the question, click on \"Add a comment\" and write your comment with the extra details.\n\nRemember, the goal is to make the question clearer and more informative for others who might want to answer or learn from it.",
